title: Fish/Prawn Culture
description: "At the Fish and Prawn Culture area, explore the sustainable practices of aquaculture. This area showcases how fish and prawns are farmed in environmentally friendly ways."

title: Feathered Place
description: "Feathered Place, where you can observe a variety of bird species in their natural habitat. This peaceful area is dedicated to bird conservation and provides a relaxing spot for bird enthusiasts."

title: Bahay Kubo
description: "Bahay Kubo, a traditional Filipino house made from native materials. This cultural icon demonstrates the principles of sustainable living and is surrounded by a variety of native plants and crops."

title: House of Greens
description: "The House of Greens, you’ll find an innovative display of sustainable greenhouse farming. Explore how advanced techniques help grow fresh vegetables and herbs in controlled environments."

title: Urban Garden
description: "The Urban Garden, a space that showcases the possibilities of gardening in urban settings. Learn about compact, vertical, and container gardening techniques for maximizing small spaces."

title: GuestHouse
description: "The Guest House, a cozy retreat for visitors looking to stay and explore the Agri-Eco Park. This serene spot offers a comfortable and inviting place for rest amidst nature."

title: Extension Hall
description: "The Extension Hall. This multifunctional space is perfect for hosting events, seminars, and gatherings. With its spacious interior, it’s a hub for agricultural learning and community interaction."

title: Agri-Eco Park Main Building
description: "The heart of the Agri-Eco Park, the Main Building. This facility is dedicated to sustainable farming practices and innovations that shape the future of eco-friendly agriculture."

title: Birds Paradise
description: "Birds Paradise, a sanctuary for colorful and exotic bird species. Listen closely and you’ll hear the chirps and calls of nature’s finest feathered friends in this peaceful aviary."

title: Poultry Village
description: "Poultry Village, where modern and traditional poultry farming methods coexist. Learn about raising chickens, ducks, and other fowl, and see how these essential animals contribute to sustainable farming."

title: Native Organics
description: "Native Organics, discover the world of organic farming with native plants. This area promotes sustainable practices that nurture our environment while producing healthy, natural crops."

title: Garden Scape
description: "Garden Scape, a delightful exhibition of creative garden designs. From vertical gardens to ornamental landscapes, get inspired to create your own green masterpiece."

title: Green Haven
description: "Green Haven, a lush, eco-friendly space where sustainability is at the forefront. Explore various environmental initiatives that make this area a green sanctuary."

title: Herb Land
description: "Herb Land awaits, filled with fragrant herbs used in both culinary and medicinal practices. Here, you can explore the scents and benefits of different herbs, from rosemary to lavender."

title: Healing Garden
description: "The Healing Garden, take a moment to unwind and reconnect with nature. This serene space promotes relaxation and healing, offering a peaceful retreat amidst the greenery."

title: Bee Program Demo Site
description: "The Bee Program Demo Site. Learn how bees play a vital role in pollination and agriculture. This area highlights the importance of bee conservation and the incredible work they do for our ecosystem."

title: Nursery
description: "The Nursery, where young plants are nurtured with care. Witness the growth process from seed to sapling, as this area supports the future of sustainable farming."

title: Theatre
description: "The Theatre, where agricultural educational programs come to life. From documentaries to live presentations, this venue offers an engaging way to learn about the world of agriculture."
